This paper deals with complexity classes and their relationship with randomness, which falls under the scope of computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it discusses the use of randomness in probabilistic algorithms. The concept of dimension is often used in the study of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM), which are relevant to this paper. Finally, the paper touches upon computational geometry (cs.CGT) as it discusses the use of geometric arguments in proving the main result.
